列挙型

enum  lex_state_bits {
  EXPR_BEG_bit, EXPR_END_bit, EXPR_ENDARG_bit, EXPR_ENDFN_bit,
  EXPR_ARG_bit, EXPR_CMDARG_bit, EXPR_MID_bit, EXPR_FNAME_bit,
  EXPR_DOT_bit, EXPR_CLASS_bit, EXPR_VALUE_bit, EXPR_LABELARG_bit,
  EXPR_MAX_STATE
}
 
enum  lex_state_e {
  EXPR_BEG = (1 << EXPR_BEG_bit), EXPR_END = (1 << EXPR_END_bit), EXPR_ENDARG = (1 << EXPR_ENDARG_bit), EXPR_ENDFN = (1 << EXPR_ENDFN_bit),
  EXPR_ARG = (1 << EXPR_ARG_bit), EXPR_CMDARG = (1 << EXPR_CMDARG_bit), EXPR_MID = (1 << EXPR_MID_bit), EXPR_FNAME = (1 << EXPR_FNAME_bit),
  EXPR_DOT = (1 << EXPR_DOT_bit), EXPR_CLASS = (1 << EXPR_CLASS_bit), EXPR_VALUE = (1 << EXPR_VALUE_bit), EXPR_LABELARG = (1 << EXPR_LABELARG_bit),
  EXPR_BEG_ANY = (EXPR_BEG | EXPR_VALUE | EXPR_MID | EXPR_CLASS | EXPR_LABELARG), EXPR_ARG_ANY = (EXPR_ARG | EXPR_CMDARG), EXPR_END_ANY = (EXPR_END | EXPR_ENDARG | EXPR_ENDFN)
}
 
enum  string_type {
  str_squote = (0), str_dquote = ( 0x02 ), str_xquote = ( 0x02 ), str_regexp = ( 0x04 | 0x01 | 0x02 ),
  str_sword = ( 0x08 ), str_dword = ( 0x08 | 0x02 ), str_ssym = ( 0x10 ), str_dsym = ( 0x10 | 0x02 )
}

12619  MEMCPY(RSTRING_PTR(_s), (_p), char, (_n)), (_s)) \

12644  case '\'': case '"': case ':': case ';':
12645  break;

12647  if (ISSPACE(*str)) break;
12648  continue;

11857  }

11864  }

11867  if (c2 == '$' || c2 == '@' || c2 == '{') {
11868  pushback(c);
11869  break;
11870  }
11871  }

11876  case '\n':
11877  if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) break;
11878  if (func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) continue;
11879  tokadd('\\');
11880  break;
11881 
11882  case '\\':
11883  if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd(c);
11884  break;
11885 
11886  case 'u':
11887  if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) {
11888  tokadd('\\');
11889  break;
11890  }

11893  func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP);

11895  mixed_escape(beg, enc, *encp);
11896  }
11897  continue;
11898

11901  if (!ISASCII(c)) {
11902  if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) tokadd('\\');
11903  goto non_ascii;
11904  }

11907  tokadd(c);
11908  continue;
11909  }

11914  mixed_escape(beg, enc, *encp);
11915  }
11916  continue;
11917  }

11919  pushback(c);
11920  if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd('\\');
11921  c = read_escape(0, &enc);
11922  }

11924  /* ignore backslashed spaces in %w */
11925  }
11926  else if (c != term && !(paren && c == paren)) {
11927  tokadd('\\');
11928  pushback(c);
11929  continue;
11930  }
11931  }
11932  }
11933  else if (!parser_isascii()) {
11934  non_ascii:
11935  has_nonascii = 1;
11936  if (enc != *encp) {
11937  mixed_error(enc, *encp);
11938  continue;
11939  }
11940  if (tokadd_mbchar(c) == -1) return -1;
11941  continue;
11942  }
11943  else if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
11944  pushback(c);
11945  break;
11946  }

11950  mixed_error(enc, *encp);
11951  continue;
11952  }
11953  }
11954  tokadd(c);
11955  }

11511 {
11512  /*
11513  * If string_literal is true, then we allow multiple codepoints
11514  * in \u{}, and add the codepoints to the current token.
11515  * Otherwise we're parsing a character literal and return a single
11516  * codepoint without adding it
11517  */
11518 
11519  int codepoint;
11520  size_t numlen;
11521 
11522  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd('\\'); tokadd('u'); }
11523 
11524  if (peek('{')) { /* handle \u{...} form */
11525  do {
11526  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd(*lex_p); }
11527  nextc();
11528  codepoint = scan_hex(lex_p, 6, &numlen);
11529  if (numlen == 0) {
11530  yyerror("invalid Unicode escape");
11531  return 0;
11532  }
11533  if (codepoint > 0x10ffff) {
11534  yyerror("invalid Unicode codepoint (too large)");
11535  return 0;
11536  }
11537  lex_p += numlen;
11538  if (regexp_literal) {
11539  tokcopy((int)numlen);
11540  }
11541  else if (codepoint >= 0x80) {
11542  *encp = rb_utf8_encoding();
11543  if (string_literal) tokaddmbc(codepoint, *encp);
11544  }
11545  else if (string_literal) {
11546  tokadd(codepoint);
11547  }
11548  } while (string_literal && (peek(' ') || peek('\t')));
11549 
11550  if (!peek('}')) {
11551  yyerror("unterminated Unicode escape");
11552  return 0;
11553  }
11554 
11555  if (regexp_literal) { tokadd('}'); }
11556  nextc();
11557  }
11558  else { /* handle \uxxxx form */
11559  codepoint = scan_hex(lex_p, 4, &numlen);
11560  if (numlen < 4) {
11561  yyerror("invalid Unicode escape");
11562  return 0;
11563  }
11564  lex_p += 4;

11566  tokcopy(4);
11567  }

11571  }
11572  else if (string_literal) {
11573  tokadd(codepoint);
11574  }
11575  }
11576 
11577  return codepoint;
11578 }

4646  /* The stacks and their tools:
4647  'yyss': related to states.
4648  'yyvs': related to semantic values.
4649 
4650  Refer to the stacks through separate pointers, to allow yyoverflow
4651  to reallocate them elsewhere. */
4652 
4653  /* The state stack. */
4654  yytype_int16 yyssa[YYINITDEPTH];

4683  Keep to zero when no symbol should be popped. */

4691 
4692  yystate = 0;
4693  yyerrstatus = 0;
4694  yynerrs = 0;

4699 | yynewstate -- Push a new state, which is found in yystate. |
4700 `------------------------------------------------------------*/
4701  yynewstate:
4702  /* In all cases, when you get here, the value and location stacks
4703  have just been pushed. So pushing a state here evens the stacks. */
4704  yyssp++;
4705 
4706  yysetstate:
4707  *yyssp = yystate;
4708 
4709  if (yyss + yystacksize - 1 <= yyssp)
4710  {
4711  /* Get the current used size of the three stacks, in elements. */
4712  YYSIZE_T yysize = yyssp - yyss + 1;
4713 
4714 #ifdef yyoverflow
4715  {
4716  /* Give user a chance to reallocate the stack. Use copies of
4717  these so that the &'s don't force the real ones into
4718  memory. */
4719  YYSTYPE *yyvs1 = yyvs;
4720  yytype_int16 *yyss1 = yyss;
4721 
4722  /* Each stack pointer address is followed by the size of the
4723  data in use in that stack, in bytes. This used to be a
4724  conditional around just the two extra args, but that might
4725  be undefined if yyoverflow is a macro. */
4726  yyoverflow (YY_("memory exhausted"),
4727  &yyss1, yysize * sizeof (*yyssp),
4728  &yyvs1, yysize * sizeof (*yyvsp),
4729  &yystacksize);
4730 
4731  yyss = yyss1;
4732  yyvs = yyvs1;
4733  }
4734 #else /* no yyoverflow */
4735 # ifndef YYSTACK_RELOCATE
4736  goto yyexhaustedlab;
4737 # else
4738  /* Extend the stack our own way. */
4739  if (YYMAXDEPTH <= yystacksize)
4740  goto yyexhaustedlab;
4741  yystacksize *= 2;
4742  if (YYMAXDEPTH < yystacksize)
4743  yystacksize = YYMAXDEPTH;
4744 
4745  {
4746  yytype_int16 *yyss1 = yyss;
4747  union yyalloc *yyptr =
4748  (union yyalloc *) YYSTACK_ALLOC (YYSTACK_BYTES (yystacksize));
4749  if (! yyptr)
4750  goto yyexhaustedlab;
4751  YYSTACK_RELOCATE (yyss_alloc, yyss);
4752  YYSTACK_RELOCATE (yyvs_alloc, yyvs);
4753 # undef YYSTACK_RELOCATE
4754  if (yyss1 != yyssa)
4755  YYSTACK_FREE (yyss1);
4756  }
4757 # endif
4758 #endif /* no yyoverflow */
4759 
4760  yyssp = yyss + yysize - 1;
4761  yyvsp = yyvs + yysize - 1;
4762 
4763  YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Stack size increased to %lu\n",
4764  (unsigned long int) yystacksize));
4765 
4766  if (yyss + yystacksize - 1 <= yyssp)
4767  YYABORT;
4768  }

4770  YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Entering state %d\n", yystate));
4771 
4772  if (yystate == YYFINAL)
4773  YYACCEPT;
4774 
4775  goto yybackup;
4776 
4777 /*-----------.
4778 | yybackup. |
4779 `-----------*/
4780 yybackup:
4781 
4782  /* Do appropriate processing given the current state. Read a
4783  lookahead token if we need one and don't already have one. */
4784 
4785  /* First try to decide what to do without reference to lookahead token. */
4786  yyn = yypact[yystate];
4787  if (yypact_value_is_default (yyn))
4788  goto yydefault;
4789 
4790  /* Not known => get a lookahead token if don't already have one. */
4791 
4792  /* YYCHAR is either YYEMPTY or YYEOF or a valid lookahead symbol. */
4793  if (yychar == YYEMPTY)
4794  {
4795  YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Reading a token: "));
4796  yychar = yylex (&yylval, parser);
4797  }
4798 
4799  if (yychar <= YYEOF)
4800  {
4801  yychar = yytoken = YYEOF;
4802  YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Now at end of input.\n"));
4803  }
4804  else
4805  {
4806  yytoken = YYTRANSLATE (yychar);
4807  YY_SYMBOL_PRINT ("Next token is", yytoken, &yylval, &yylloc);
4808  }
4809 
4810  /* If the proper action on seeing token YYTOKEN is to reduce or to
4811  detect an error, take that action. */
4812  yyn += yytoken;
4813  if (yyn < 0 || YYLAST < yyn || yycheck[yyn] != yytoken)
4814  goto yydefault;
4815  yyn = yytable[yyn];
4816  if (yyn <= 0)
4817  {
4818  if (yytable_value_is_error (yyn))
4819  goto yyerrlab;
4820  yyn = -yyn;
4821  goto yyreduce;
4822  }
4823 
4824  /* Count tokens shifted since error; after three, turn off error
4825  status. */
4826  if (yyerrstatus)
4827  yyerrstatus--;
4828 
4829  /* Shift the lookahead token. */
4830  YY_SYMBOL_PRINT ("Shifting", yytoken, &yylval, &yylloc);
4831 
4832  /* Discard the shifted token. */
4833  yychar = YYEMPTY;
4834 
4835  yystate = yyn;
4836  YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_BEGIN
4837  *++yyvsp = yylval;
4838  YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_END
4839 
4840  goto yynewstate;
4841 
4842 
4843 /*-----------------------------------------------------------.
4844 | yydefault -- do the default action for the current state. |
4845 `-----------------------------------------------------------*/
4846 yydefault:
4847  yyn = yydefact[yystate];
4848  if (yyn == 0)
4849  goto yyerrlab;
4850  goto yyreduce;
4851 
4852 
4853 /*-----------------------------.
4854 | yyreduce -- Do a reduction. |
4855 `-----------------------------*/
4856 yyreduce:
4857  /* yyn is the number of a rule to reduce with. */
4858  yylen = yyr2[yyn];
4859 
4860  /* If YYLEN is nonzero, implement the default value of the action:
4861  '$$ = $1'.
4862 
4863  Otherwise, the following line sets YYVAL to garbage.
4864  This behavior is undocumented and Bison

14887 {

14892  }

14894  switch (nd_type(node)) {

4481  const char *yyformat = YY_NULLPTR;
4482  /* Arguments of yyformat. */
4483  char const *yyarg[YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM];
4484  /* Number of reported tokens (one for the "unexpected", one per
4485  "expected"). */
4486  int yycount = 0;
4487 
4488  /* There are many possibilities here to consider:
4489  - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
4490  the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
4491  is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
4492  tokens because there are none.
4493  - The only way there can be no lookahead present (in yychar) is if
4494  this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
4495  detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
4496  that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
4497  case, just report a simple "syntax error".
4498  - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
4499  consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
4500  previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
4501  action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
4502  - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
4503  correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
4504  to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
4505  scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
4506  (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
4507  token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
4508  one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
4509  accepted due to an error action in a later state.
4510  */
4511  if (yytoken != YYEMPTY)

4519  this state because they are default actions. */
